## GitHub API Integration Rules

- Target endpoint: `GET https://api.github.com/users/luisalarcon-gauntlet/repos?per_page=100&sort=updated`
- Pinned repos endpoint: `GET https://api.github.com/users/luisalarcon-gauntlet/repos` (sort by pushed_at, handle pinned client-side by starring logic or updated order)
- Backend exposes exactly one endpoint to frontend: `GET /api/repos`
- Response shape must include per repo: `name`, `description`, `html_url`, `language`, `topics`, `stargazers_count`, `updated_at`
- Strip all other fields before sending to frontend — do not proxy raw GitHub response

---

## API Contract (Frontend ↔ Backend)

```
GET /api/repos
Response 200:
{
  "repos": [
    {
      "name": string,
      "description": string | null,
      "html_url": string,
      "language": string | null,
      "topics": string[],
      "stargazers_count": number,
      "updated_at": string  // ISO 8601
    }
  ],
  "cached": boolean,
  "fetched_at": string  // ISO 8601
}

GET /api/health
Response 200: { "status": "ok" }
```

No other endpoints in v1.

