## docker-compose Rules

- `docker-compose.yml` at repo root is the only way to run the full stack
- All three services must start with `docker-compose up` — no manual steps
- Services:
  - `db`: postgres:15-alpine, volume-mounted, health check required
  - `backend`: built from `./backend/Dockerfile`, depends_on `db`, port 8000
  - `frontend`: built from `./frontend/Dockerfile`, depends_on `backend`, port 3000
- Environment variables passed via `environment:` block in docker-compose — no `.env` files committed
- Backend `DATABASE_URL` and `GITHUB_USERNAME` must be env vars, not hardcoded in Python files
- Frontend `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL` must point to `http://backend:8000` inside Docker network

---

## Build Order — Happy Path First

Build in this exact order. Do not move to the next step until the current one works end-to-end.

1. **docker-compose + Postgres** — `db` service starts, accepts connections, health check passes
2. **FastAPI skeleton** — `GET /api/health` returns 200, backend container starts cleanly
3. **GitHub API fetch** — backend calls GitHub, returns raw repo data (no cache yet)
4. **Postgres caching** — cache miss/hit logic works, `repo_cache` table created on startup
5. **`GET /api/repos` endpoint** — returns stripped, shaped response per contract above
6. **Next.js project scaffold** — `frontend` container starts, renders blank page at `localhost:3000`
7. **Projects grid** — fetches `/api/repos`, renders cards with name, description, language, tags, stars, date, link
8. **Hero section** — static: name, title, bio, GitHub link, LinkedIn link
9. **About section** — static: short paragraph, resume download link
10. **Contact section** — static: email link, GitHub, LinkedIn
11. **Dark theme + responsive layout** — Tailwind dark theme applied across all sections
12. **Full `docker-compose up` smoke test** — all three containers healthy, page loads, repos display

