## What NOT to Build in v1

- No admin panel, no auth, no login
- No blog section
- No analytics (no Google Analytics, no Vercel Analytics)
- No contact form — email link only
- No custom domain configuration
- No complex error boundary UI — if the API fails, show nothing or a single line of text
- No loading skeletons — a simple loading state or nothing is fine
- No unit tests, no e2e tests — ship working code first
- No CI/CD pipeline — out of scope
- No dark/light mode toggle — dark only

---

## Code Quality Rules

- Every file has a single, obvious responsibility
- No files over 200 lines — split before you reach it
- No `any` types in TypeScript — type everything from the API contract
- Python functions do one thing — no god functions in `github.py` or `repos.py`
- Comments explain *why*, not *what* — the code explains what
- If something feels complicated, it is — simplify before committing